article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 93, Austin Peay 54
article.story: FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. -- Eddie Williams scored 25 points to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 93-54 victory Friday night over Austin Peay. Williams hit 69 percent of his shots from the field -- 11-of-16 -- setting the pace for a team that made 67 percent of its field-goal attempts in the second half of the game, the second in the Jim Thorpe Classic hosted by Arkansas. The Lumberjacks (7-2) led 41-31 at intermission, but held Austin Peay (5-5) to just 28 percent shooting in the second half to turn the game into a rout. Josh Alexander scored 16 points for Stephen F. Austin, Matt Kingsley added 13, plus eight rebounds, and Walt Harris scored 11. Drake Reed was the only player for the Governors to score in double digist, with 16 points.
